SEO
![alt text](image-7.png)

https://www.flipkart.com/sitemap
https://www.flipkart.com/robots.txt -> what are the pages to crawl, and what are not important, what are allowed and not allowed, what are the pages to index.
# cart
User-agent: *
Disallow: /viewcart -> this means it will not index these and are not allowed the webpage to access/show

# Something related to carousel and recommendation carousel
User-agent: *
Disallow: /dynamic/

https://www.amazon.in/robots.txt
Disallow: /gp/registry/wishlist/
Disallow: /wishlist/
Allow: /wishlist/universal* -> ![alt text](image-5.png)
Allow: /wishlist/vendor-button*
Allow: /wishlist/get-button*

Canonical: If there are 5 duplicate page, web crawler gets confused, so canonical will inform which is original one
![alt text](image-6.png)

